╭─ assistant [MainThread@4081953] ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation occurs because a plain compare in a non-dedicated exit block (multiple predecessors) gets folded to a constant, turning the ret into true. A minimal,         │
│ targeted fix is to add a conservative guard in checkAndReplaceCondition for CmpInsts: before attempting to fold the compare, bail out if its parent block has 2 or more predecessors.     │
│ This avoids folding in shared exit blocks while preserving optimizations elsewhere.                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp | sed -n '1418,1436p' && sed -i '1426a\  if (Cmp->getParent() && Cmp->getParent()->hasNPredecessorsOrMore(2)) return false;'  │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp && submit-patch                                                                                                                      │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                       │
