│ THOUGHT: The broad predecessor-count guard caused many tests to fail. A more precise fix is to skip folding only when the compare is directly used by a ReturnInst in a block with        │
│ multiple predecessors (the non-dedicated exit case from the issue). I will add a targeted guard in the plain compare folding path: before checkCondition, detect if any user is a         │
│ ReturnInst in the compare’s parent block, and if that block has 2 or more predecessors, bail out. This prevents miscompiling shared exits while preserving other optimizations.           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ python3 - << 'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np = Path('llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp')\ns = p.read_text()\nanchor = '  if (auto ImpliedCondition =\\n              │
│ checkCondition(Cmp->getPredicate(), Cmp->getOperand(0),\\n                         Cmp->getOperand(1), Cmp, Info))'\ninsert = '  // Avoid folding compares used by a return in            │
│ non-dedicated exit blocks.\\n  // If the compare feeds a ReturnInst in a block with multiple predecessors,\\n  // folding it to a constant can change semantics when the condition does   │
│ not\\n  // hold for all incoming edges.\\n  if (auto *ParentBB = Cmp->getParent()) {\\n    if (ParentBB->hasNPredecessorsOrMore(2)) {\\n      for (User *U : Cmp->users()) {\\n        if │
│ (auto *RI = dyn_cast<ReturnInst>(U)) {\\n          if (RI->getParent() == ParentBB)\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n'\n# Insert the guard just before   │
│ the checkCondition anchor\ns = s.replace(anchor, insert + anchor)\np.write_text(s)\nprint('Applied targeted non-dedicated-exit guard for return-users.')\nPY\n && submit-patch```         │
